China Stocks: China Coal, Pang Da Auto, Shenhua Energy

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-17T07:51:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/baoshan-iron-steel-pangda-automobile-china-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are as of the 3 p.m. close.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, rose 3.71 points, or 0.1 percent, to
2,852.77. The  CSI 300 Index (SHSZ300)  gained 0.5 percent to 3,116.03.  Coal producers: China Shenhua Energy Co. (601088 CH), the
nation’s largest coal producer, surged 2.3 percent to 28.27
yuan, its biggest gain since April 21. China Coal Energy Co.
(601898 CH), the second largest, advanced 2.1 percent to 10.29
yuan. Shanxi Guoyang New Energy Co. (600348 CH) jumped the 10
percent daily limit to 23.78 yuan.  Coal stocks rose on speculation prices of the fuel will
rally as the nation’s power shortage boosts demand.  “The rebound is based on solid demand from downstream
industries and also the recent power shortage,” said Liu
Zhaoliang, analyst at Qilu Securities Ltd.  Pang Da Automobile Trade Co. (601258 CH), China’s biggest
listed auto dealer, advanced 3.4 percent to 35.17 yuan, its
biggest gain since its listing in April. The company said it
agreed to buy a 24 percent stake in Spyker Cars NV.  Xinhu Zhongbao Co. (600208 CH), a property developer,
dropped 2.5 percent to 5.97 yuan after saying it bought two
parcels of land in Zhejiang province for 289.9 million yuan ($45
million) at auctions.  --Zhang Shidong. With assistance from Winnie Zhu in  Shanghai .
